ý","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Zesnulý","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Zesnulá","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie","England":"Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1250–":"1250–Afdød","1250–Male":"1250–Afdød","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Afdød","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Afdød","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1250–":"1250–Overleden","1250–Male":"1250–Overleden","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Overleden","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Overleden","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1250–":"1250–Deceased","1250–Male":"1250–Deceased","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Deceased","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Deceased","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Raleigh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Raleigh (House) in Pilton (Devon), recorded as <i>Radeleia</i> in 1086 and <i>Rawlegh</i> in 1535. The placename probably derives from Old English <i>rǣge</i> ‘roe deer’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: variant of   Riley  .","History: The English explorer Sir Walter Raleigh (1554–1618) was born in Hayes Barton, Devon, into a family of Devon gentry. He was related to most of the West Country's important families, including that of Sir Francis Drake. His half-brother was the explorer Sir Humphrey Gilbert. In 1578 Raleigh was granted a patent to explore and colonize “unknown lands” in America. In the 1580s he was granted extensive estates in Munster (Ireland), in reward for his suppression of the Desmond Rebellions."],"variants":[{"name":"Raley","meanings":["English: variant of   Raleigh  ."]},{"name":"Rawleigh","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Erwin, Orlo.","English: variant of   Raleigh  , reflecting a common pronunciation."]},{"name":"Riley","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): habitational name chiefly from High Ryley in Accrington (Lancashire) and Riley in Kirkburton, which was in the manor of Wakefield (Yorkshire). In some cases the name may derive from Riley Farm in Eyam (Derbyshire), Royley in Royton (Lancashire), or Rylah in Scarcliffe (Derbyshire). The placenames all come from Old English <i>rȳge</i> ‘rye’ + <i>lēah</i> ‘woodland clearing’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Raghailligh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Raghailleach</i>’, Old Irish <i>Roghallach</i>. This is the name of a chieftain family in Cavan, related to the O'Rourkes. In Anglicized form it has also been confused with <b>Ó Raithile</b> found in Munster, usually Anglicized as <b>O'Rahilly</b> or   Rahilly  . See   O'Reilly  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Raleigh was born in 1250, in Farleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Raleigh, was 25 and his mother, Joan de Stockhay, was 20. He had at least 2 sons with Lora Peverel. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1250–":"1250–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Surnud","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1250–":"1250–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Kuollut","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1250–":"1250–Décédé","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Décédé","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Thomas Raleigh est né en 1250, à Farleigh, Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, William Raleigh, avait 25 ans et sa mère, Joan de Stockhay, avait 20 ans. Il a eu au moins 2 fils avec Lora Peverel. Il est décédé à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1250–":"1250–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1254–1326":"1254–1326","1275–Male":"1275–Verstorben","–1275":"–1275","1225–1270":"1225–1270","1230–Female":"1230–Verstorben","1326":"1326","1225":"1225","1254":"1254","1275":"1275","1230":"1230","1250":"1250","1270":"1270","Raleigh, Devon, England":"Devon, England","England":"England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Thomas Raleigh 1250 in Farleigh, Devon, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war sein Vater William Raleigh 25 und seine Mutter Joan de Stockhay 20. Er hatte mit Lora Peverel mindestens 2 Sö